    "analysis": "Previous step: telemetry files were loaded and summarized. Counts: metric.csv rows=8969, trace.csv rows=18656, log.csv rows=2196, error_logs.csv rows=0. Available KPI names in metric.csv include: cpu, diskio, error, latency-50, latency-90, mem, socket, workload. Trace and log files contain many service-level entries including ts-auth-service, ts-order-service, ts-route-service, ts-travel-service, but metric.csv only contained a subset of services. Of the five possible root-cause components (ts-auth-service, ts-order-service, ts-route-service, ts-train-service, ts-travel-service), only ts-auth-service is present in metric.csv summary; the others may be missing from metrics but are present in traces/logs. To follow the required workflow, next we should compute global thresholds (P95) for the available candidate component(s) in metric.csv using the full series, then filter to the incident window and detect anomalies there. This will narrow down metric-level faults to guide subsequent trace/log analysis.",
